02:12.759 --> 02:26.642
And let me read it in my goal for tonight is to be sort of repetitive and get one simple truth across, namely this verse.

02:27.042 --> 02:34.851
that God's zeal for his name or his fame is the foundation of your hope as a sinner.

02:36.532 --> 02:51.769
Because I think if you can add that to your storehouse of biblical insight and knowledge, you'll have another piece of artillery with which to defeat the lies and the attacks of the devil.

02:51.849 --> 02:56.434
So here's a verse that has ministered to me so significantly, and I hope we'll

02:56.866 --> 03:00.632
do so to you and then we'll pray and jump into the questions.

03:02.474 --> 03:23.826
Ezekiel 2044, God speaking, you shall know that I am the Lord when I deal with you for my namesake, not according to your evil ways, nor according to your corrupt doings, O house of Israel, says the Lord.

03:25.954 --> 03:38.167
You shall know that I am the Lord when I deal with you according to or for the sake of my name and not according to your evil ways."

03:38.668 --> 03:41.311
So God had in front of him two ways to treat his people.

03:42.352 --> 03:48.799
He could treat them according to their evil ways or he could treat them for his namesake.

03:50.140 --> 03:51.962
Those are the two options set up in this verse.

