26:04.001 --> 26:06.766
It pleased the Lord to make you a people for himself.

26:07.727 --> 26:19.105
And now when you are threatened, something is at stake in God more than just his commitment to you.

26:20.607 --> 26:22.450
What's at stake is his name.

26:23.554 --> 26:24.575
That's what's implied here.

26:24.895 --> 26:30.702
For his namesake, he won't cast you away because he made you a people for himself.

26:30.762 --> 26:33.565
So evidently, here's the way I would, maybe I can draw it.

26:35.407 --> 26:43.175
There are levels in God's commitments, and they're all rooted in a deep, most fundamental root commitment.

26:43.195 --> 26:53.106
And that tap root, I think, is God's love for his

26:53.634 --> 26:54.054
name.

26:56.057 --> 26:57.278
That's the tap root.

26:57.318 --> 27:03.525
You can't go lower in the being of God than that.

27:04.586 --> 27:07.409
God loves being God.

27:09.471 --> 27:20.563
Thank you for listening to this episode of Light and Truth, where we are committed to providing God-centered preaching to help you see Christ clearly and treasure Him truly.

27:21.264 --> 27:22.866
I'm your host, Dan Kruver.

27:23.554 --> 27:34.139
On our next episode, John Piper concludes our two-part series for God's namesake with a teaching titled, Why God Seeks Your Joy.

27:34.861 --> 27:35.703
I hope you'll join us.

27:36.665 --> 27:40.274
For more resources, visit desiringgod.org.

